  "title": "Senior Financial Analyst (Assistant Manager)",
  "description": "<p>Responsibilities:</p><p><br /></p><p>• Provide management with timely financial analysis and recommendations across a range of critical business decisions</p><p>• Provide analysis and supporting commentary on the variances between actual and budget/forecast</p><p>• Monthly P&L outcome to Business Unit Heads</p><p>• Partner the business units to formulate key strategies and recommendations to drive growth and profitability</p><p>• Provide management with financial insights on market conditions and trends</p><p>• Perform financial due diligence</p><p>• Strengthen current internal controls and improve Finance processes and systems</p><p><br /></p><p>Requirements:</p><ul><li>Hold a Bachelor’s degree in accountancy or possess an ACCA or equivalent qualification</li><li>Minimum 5-8 years of relevant Financial Planning and Analysis experience</li><li>Candidates with prior audit experience in a public accounting firm and commercial experience are preferred.</li><li>Demonstrate meticulousness, able to work efficiently under strict timelines, and possess an investigative mindset.</li></ul><p>Please email your CV directly in Word format to: <a href=\"mailto:commerce@theedgepartnership.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">brendan@theedgepartnership.com</a></p><p><br /></p><p>Please note that only shortlisted candidates will be contacted due to the high number of applications.</p><p>EA License: 16S8131</p><p><br /></p><p>Recruiter License: R1104469</p>",
